chunk_content: Cause of death definitions: • HIV disease resulting in TB: Any patient with known or presumed TB (pulmonary and/or extra- pulmonary) at the time of death without another identified COD • HIV disease resulting in other infectious and parasitic disease: Any patient who died from any infectious cause other than TB; this includes infections not otherwise specified • HIV disease resulting in cancer: Any patient with known or presumed cancer at the time of death • Other HIV disease, resulting in other diseases or conditions leading to death: Any patient who died from a non-infectious, non-malignant cause that was related to HIV, such as acute HIV infection syndrome, (persistent) generalized lymphadenopathy, hematological and immunological abnormalities, etc. • Other natural causes: Any patient who died from natural causes (including certain cancers and infections, etc.) that were not directly related to HIV disease.
